{title: Deep In The Heart Of Texas}
{artist: Hank Thompson}
{composer: Written by Don Swander and June Hershey}

[C]The stars at night are big and bright
Deep in the heart of [G7]Texas
The prairie sky is wide and high
Deep in the heart of [C]Texas
The Sage in bloom is like perfume
Deep in the heart of [G7]Texas
Reminds me of the one I love
Deep in the heart of [C]Texas
The cowboys cry ki-yip-pie-yi
Deep in the heart of [G7]Texas
The rabbits rush around the brush
Deep in the heart of [C]Texas
The coyotes wail along the trail
Deep in the heart of [G7]Texas
The doggies bawl and bawl and bawl
Deep in the heart of [C]Texas